-- Heavy case load may lead Brazil top court to postpone bank ruling
-- By Aluísio Alves
-- Tue May 27, 2014 11:39AM EDT
-- None



SAO PAULO, May 27 (Reuters) - A heavy case load at Brazil's Federal Supreme Court means that a ruling on a landmark savings case dating back more than two decades could end up being postponed until after the October presidential election, court Justice Marco Aurelio Mello told Reuters on Tuesday.   (Reporting by Aluísio Alves; Writing by  Guillermo Parra-Bernal, Editing by Franklin Paul)  ((guillermo.parra@thomsonreuters.com)(+55-11-5644-7714)(+55-119 -8346-7153)(Reuters Messaging: guillermo.parra.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: BRAZIL BANKS/RULING

